Kaduna State Governor, Malam Nasir El-Rufai yesterday said he was still under isolation for testing positive to COVID-19 and is yet to be cleared of the disease. El-Rufai who also chaired a virtual meeting of the State Executive Council for the first time since he was diagnosed urged Nigerians to ignore any report insinuating that he was cleared of the disease and assured that he would personally announce the news when he is confirmed negative. The Governor stated via his tweeter account that; “Earlier Wednesday 10am-2pm, I took a few hours during isolation to chair a virtual meeting of the State Executive Council. I haven’t been cleared of COVID-19 yet and will personally announce when confirmed negative. Ignore fake news even if you like it.” I am still COVID-19 positive, El-Rufai speaks from isolation COVID-19 exposure: Many govs refuse to self-isolate COVID-19: Status of 20 Nigerian governors unknown